title: For Sale:  S&W model 686-3 2.5" Stainless Snubby Safe Queen
postcontent: The J frame makes a great concealed carry 5 round back up revolver for .38 special. The K frame holds six rounds, and is larger. The extra size and weight makes it more accurate. In fact, back in the day --- The Police carried this! It was known for shooting .38 special at the range; and carrying .357 for business. S&W came out with the next model. The "L" frame. It is heavier and thicker, as it was designed for a steady diet of .357 Magnum The 686 model is an L frame, designed to be stronger for Heavy Bone Crushing Magnum Loads for hunting. Although it is a bit heavier and wider than a K frame - in the Snubby round butt version; it can be carried concealed with .38 special hollow points. What makes a 1988 revolver better than a newer version? 1) The firing pin is on the trigger 2) Case hardened - Flash chromed Forged trigger and Target hammer 3) No modern Mim (weak) parts 4) No Internal Lock. 5) Easy to use. Hold tight, aim, pull trigger. No 500 round break in is required to trust it. Yes, this was built when Quality still mattered. Today's guns are about mass production short cuts, no hand fitting and keeping the price cheap. That is why you can't give away a new revolver, and the older guns fetch a premium price. This super shiny personal bodyguard sports a beautiful pair of S&W Walnut grips. Put it next to your Glock and see which one your eyes keep darting towards! Plastic Tupperware does not have the Romance of the Old Cowboy days. They belong in an Easy Bake Oven. This 686-3 belongs on your Open Carry BBQ Holster! Compare the single action pull to a 1911. Just as sweet. The double action is better to survive the Legal aftermath of a warranted shooting, with a pull much smoother than a Plastic double safe trigger Brick. I am not a dealer. My guns listed for sale took me decades to collect. They are my babies, my toys, my safe queens. My carry gun is a Glock 23, with a grip chewed on by my Bulldog Puppy. Safe Queens sit in my safe, and get rotated to my living room display case with polishing and oiling. I keep them like new. Who cares if a Glock gets dirty or becomes an English Bully chew toy? They are not attractive, but they do go bang…. The reason I am selling part of my Safe Queen collection is due to Hurricane Irma damaging my roof, blowing down my fence; frying my well pump; etc. at my N. FL farm home, and S. FL townhome. Insurance will not cover the cost of a fence on 20 acres… They will not apply the cost to the deductible. FEMA is no help if you have a job and own stuff. So….. (sniff) I have to cull the collection. Here is your chance to own a gorgeous piece of history that will Double in value. Good Luck with your bid. Gun comes with the original Rubber Grip and a black soft range carry bag. Wood grips are the Rare Hogue Combat Walnut that came on the old model 66 F Comp. Sorry, the box and paperwork got ruined in the attic when the roof blew off in the hurricane.
